<HL>
   Business Brief -- Thomson Corp.:
   KKR Affiliate to Acquire
   Thomson Corp. Unit Assets
</HL>
<DATE>
05/08/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   T.TOC
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   An affiliate of New York investment bank Kohlberg Kravis
Roberts &amp; Co. agreed to acquire the assets of Thomson Corp.'s
Ward's Communications subsidiary, a provider of auto-industry
data.
   Terms weren't disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The buyer, K-III Holdings, includes Intertec Publishing
Corp., a publisher of trade magazines and technical books;
Macmillan Book Clubs Inc., an operator of professional book
clubs; and K-III Press Inc., a provider of information to the
rail, trucking and ocean-freight industries.
   Thomson, based in Toronto, has interests in newspapers,
specialty publishing and travel.
</TEXT>
